===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

In oracle bone script, it may be written as {{och-l|𡵂}} or {{och-l|𢼸}}. 

The former is a variant of {{och-l|美}}, borrowed for sound, {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a person with long hair. 

The latter an {{Han compound|nocap=y|美|alt1=𡵂|攴|alt2=攵|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=hand with tool}} – splitting or combing hairs; minute. Possibly the original form of {{och-l|媺}}. 

{{och-l|彳}} was added to emphasize action to create the modern form.

===Etymology 1===
; "not; no"
: The negative root ''*m'' + {{och-l|惟|to be}} ({{zh-ref|Pulleybank, 1995}}).
; "small"
